name: Janna
title: the Storm's Fury
lore: Armed with the power of Runeterra's gales, Janna is a mysterious, elemental wind spirit who protects the dispossessed of Zaun. Some believe she was brought into existence by the pleas of Runeterra's sailors who prayed for fair winds as they navigated treacherous waters and braved rough tempests. Her favor and protection has since been called into the depths of Zaun, where Janna has become a beacon of hope to those in need. No one knows where or when she will appear, but more often than not, she's come to help.
blurb: Armed with the power of Runeterra's gales, Janna is a mysterious, elemental wind spirit who protects the dispossessed of Zaun. Some believe she was brought into existence by the pleas of Runeterra's sailors who prayed for fair winds as they navigated...
allytips: Eye of the Storm can be used on allied turrets.
Quickly firing a Howling Gale without the charge up can be used to heavily disable the other team.
Timing Janna's ultimate can push enemies away from a wounded ally or even separate enemies.
enemytips: Save an interrupt ability for when Janna uses her ultimate.
Listen for the charge up sound on Howling Gale in case Janna is trying to hit you with it from off screen or from brush.
Janna's at her strongest when buffing another ally. If you can harass her ally, it will weaken her ability to fight you.

riot_spells.name: Howling Gale
riot_spells.description: By creating a localized change in pressure and temperature, Janna is able to create a small storm that grows in size with time. She can activate the spell again to release the storm. On release this storm will fly towards the direction it was cast in, dealing damage and knocking away any enemies in its path.
riot_spells.tooltip:
Summons a whirlwind, which deals {{ e1 }} (+{{ a1 }}) magic damage to enemies in its path and knocks them into the air for {{ e4 }} seconds.

The whirlwind can be charged up to {{ e6 }} seconds. For each second charged, it:
  • Deals {{ e2 }} (+{{ a2 }}) bonus damage
  • Knocks up for an additional {{ e5 }} seconds
  • Travels {{ e3 }}% further
Howling Gale always reaches its destination in {{ e8 }} seconds.

Activate again to release the whirlwind early.

riot_spells.name: Zephyr
riot_spells.description: Janna summons an air elemental that passively increases her Movement Speed and enables her to pass through units. She may also activate this ability to deal damage and slow an enemy's Movement Speed. The passive is lost while this ability is on cooldown.
riot_spells.tooltip:
Passive: While Zephyr is not on cooldown, Janna gains {{ e1 }}% (+{{ f1 }}%) Movement Speed and can move through units.

Active: Deals {{ e2 }} (+{{ a1 }}) (+{{ f3 }}) magic damage to an enemy and slows their Movement Speed by {{ e3 }}% (+{{ f2 }}%) for {{ e4 }} seconds.

riot_spells.name: Eye Of The Storm
riot_spells.description: Janna conjures a defensive gale that shields an ally champion or turret from incoming damage and increases their Attack Damage.
riot_spells.tooltip:
Grants an allied champion or turret a shield that decays over {{ e3 }} seconds. The shield absorbs up to {{ e1 }} (+{{ a1 }}) damage and grants {{ e2 }} (+{{ a2 }}) attack damage until it is fully depleted.

Each Janna ability that slows or knocks an enemy champion airborne will reduce Eye of the Storm's cooldown by {{ ecdrefundforcc*100 }}%.

riot_spells.name: Monsoon
riot_spells.description: Janna surrounds herself in a magical storm, throwing enemies back. After the storm has settled, soothing winds heal nearby allies while the ability is active.
riot_spells.tooltip: Summons forth the might of the wind to knock surrounding enemies back and restores {{ e1 }} (+{{ a1 }}) Health to nearby allies each second for {{ e3 }} seconds.

riot_passive.name: Tailwind
riot_passive.description:
Janna passively gains 8% Movement Speed, and nearby allied champions gain this bonus when moving toward her.

Additionally, Janna's basic attacks cause additional magic damage based on her bonus Movement Speed.

i1.name: Tailwind
i1.blurb: Janna passively gains 8% Movement Speed, and nearby allied champions gain this bonus when moving toward her. Additionally, Janna's basic attacks cause additional magic damage based on her bonus Movement Speed.
i1.description: {{sbc|Innate:}} '''Janna''' passively gains {{sti|ms|{{as|8% '''bonus''' movement speed}}}} and grants the same amount to nearby allied [[champion]]s moving towards her.
i1.description2: '''Janna's''' [[basic attack]]s and {{ai|Zephyr|Janna}} deal bonus [[on-hit]] {{as|magic damage}} equal to {{as|{{pp|2|key=%|25;35|1;10}} of her '''bonus''' {{sti|[[movement speed]]}}}}.
i1.notes: * Considering '''Janna's''' base movement speed of {{data Janna|pst2|ms}}, she actually has a starting movement speed of {{tt|{{fd|{{#expr:{{data Janna|pst2|ms}}*1.08}}}}|{{data Janna|pst2|ms}}{{times}}1.08}} thus granting {{pp|2|{{data Janna|pst2|ms}}*0.08*0.25;{{data Janna|pst2|ms}}*0.08*0.35|1;10}} bonus on-hit magic damage.

q1.name: Howling Gale
q1.blurb: By creating a localized change in pressure and temperature, Janna is able to create a small storm that grows in size with time. She can activate the spell again to release the storm. On release this storm will fly towards the direction it was cast in, dealing damage and knocking away any enemies in its path.
q1.description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Janna''' summons a whirlwind at her current location which charges up over 3 seconds. Its range, speed, damage, and {{tip|airborne|knockup}} duration increase for each second it is left charging.
q1.leveling:
{{st|Minimum Magic Damage|{{ap|60 to 160}} {{as|(+ 35% AP)}}}}<!--
-->{{st|Bonus Magic Damage Per Second|{{ap|15 to 35}} {{as|(+ 10% AP)}}|Maximum Magic Damage|{{ap|60+15*3 to 160+35*3}} {{as|(+ 65% AP)}}}}
q1.description2: At the end of the duration, or upon reactivation, the whirlwind launches itself for {{fd|1.5}} seconds in the target direction, dealing {{as|magic damage}} to all enemies it passes through and {{tip|airborne|knocking them up}} for {{pp|7|type=seconds charged|0.5 to 1.25|0 to 3|formula=0.5+(0.125 per half second).}} seconds.
q1.target_range: {{pp|7|type=seconds charged|1000 to 1000*1.75|0 to 3|formula=1000+(125 per half second).}}
q1.speed: {{pp|7|type=seconds charged|1000*2/3 to 1000*2/3*1.75|0 to 3|formula=666.7+(83.3 per half second).}}
q1.notes:
* ''Howling Gale'' has no cast time and does not interrupt '''Janna's''' previous orders.
* The storm does not interact with enemy units that stand on top of it while it is charging.

e1.name: Eye of the Storm
e1.blurb: Janna conjures a defensive gale that shields an ally champion or turret from incoming damage and increases their Attack Damage.
e1.description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Janna''' {{tip|shields}} the target allied champion or herself for 5 seconds, decaying over the duration after {{fd|0.75}} seconds.
e1.description2: While the shield holds, her target gains {{as|'''bonus''' attack damage}}.
e1.description3: Each ability that {{tip|slow|slows}} or {{tip|airborne|knocks}} an enemy champion airborne reduces ''Eye of the Storm's'' cooldown by 20%, up to once per ability cast.
e1.description4: ''Eye of the Storm'' can be used on turrets, causing '''Janna''' to be credited for any champion kills it earns while the shield holds.
e1.notes:
* ''Eye of the Storm'' has no cast time and does not interrupt Janna's previous orders.
* Allied turrets will benefit from the bonus attack damage when targeted by ''Eye of the Storm''.

r1.name: Monsoon
r1.blurb: Janna surrounds herself in a magical storm, throwing enemies back. After the storm has settled, soothing winds heal nearby allies while the ability is active.
r1.description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Janna''' {{tip|channels}} for 3 seconds, {{tip|airborne|knocking back}} all nearby enemies up to 875 units based on their proximity to her, while {{tip|stun|stunning}} them for {{fd|0.5}} seconds.
r1.description2: While channeling, she releases soothing winds that {{tip|heal}} nearby allies every half-second.
r1.notes:
* ''Monsoon'' can be used to pseudo-stun enemy champions pushed into a wall before the knockback travels its full distance.
* {{tip|Spell shield}} will block the knockback.
